## The gateway nobody expects

Convergence points the agent discovered by tracing a flow end to end. Where do many paths funnel to one function? Note the exact file and the routes that lead there.

Example:

> ALL file open paths converge at `editorService.openEditor()` in `src/vs/.../editor/browser/editorService.ts`. Explorer click, Cmd+O, extensions, command palette: all land here. If you are debugging file open, start here, not the explorer.

## Gotchas that will bite you

Subtle ordering bugs, silent validation skips, places where the code says one thing and the runtime does another. Surfaced by [`../experiments/understanding-test.md`](../experiments/understanding-test.md).

Example:

> `URI.revive()` (used in tab restoration and cross process IPC) bypasses all normalization and validation. `URI.from()` silently fixes paths. `URI.revive()` doesn't. If you are debugging weird URI state after restart, this is why.

## Code navigation

Layering conventions, naming conventions, where to find the implementation when you have the interface.

Example:

> `common/` holds interfaces. `browser/` holds implementations. ALWAYS check `browser/` when you find an interface in `common/`. The class is usually the same name minus the leading `I`.

## Tests

The right command. The right runner. Common test framework pitfalls.

Example:

> `suite()` / `test()`, NOT `describe()` / `it()`. `describe` / `it` silently passes but doesn't register the tests.
>
>     node test/unit/node/index.js --run 'src/vs/...'

